Product Description

Read more

Duo Evo Plus 10-in-1 Multi Pressure Cooker

It's a pressure cooker, rice cooker, slow cooker, yogurt maker, steamer, sous vide, sauté, food warmer, cake maker, and stock pot

This latest generation Instant Pot takes you from dinner to dessert, all with the touch of a button. Homemade soup, mouth-watering sous vide, a side of rice and steamed vegetables, and of course the perfect cake.

The Duo Evo Plus multi cooker is easy to use, easy to clean, fast, versatile and convenient with the capacity you need to feed your family and impress your guests. The 10-in-1 Duo Evo Plus is a pressure cooker, rice cooker, slow cooker, yogurt maker, steamer, sous vide, sauté, food warmer, cake maker, and stock pot. Plus, its 48 pre-sets take the guesswork out of cooking. You can get nutritious dinners on the table quicker with cooking times up to 70% faster than traditional methods.

Smart Programs include:

Pressure cook, grain/rice, slow cook, yogurt maker, steam, sous vide, sauté, keep warn & bake.

Plus, its 48 pre-sets take the guesswork out of cooking. You can get nutritious dinners on the table quicker with cooking times up to 70% faster than traditional methods.

Specifications

  • Size options: 5.7L only
  • 10 One Touch Smart Programs
  • Power: 1200W
  • Power Supply: 220-240V
  • Weight: 5.9kg
  • Accessories included: steam rack with handles and spare sealing ring
  • Dimensions: 33.1L x 32.2W x 32.5H
Read more

Features & Benefits:

48 New Preset Functions

All you need right at your fingertips.

All the features of the Duo , plus more

Come complete with a progress indicator on the display screen giving you everything you need to know.

Easy Grip Handles

The inner pot that can be used on all hobs including induction and easy-grip handles let you move between appliances as recipes demand.

Easy Seal Lid

The new pressure cooker lid automatically seals when in place. Just listen for the jingle and then go and relax.

Read more

Easy as 1-2-3

Take the guess work out of cooking. The large LCD display provides everything you need to know about cooking time, temperature, pressure and status, among others. Time to start cooking:

  1. Press a button to select a Smart Program
  2. Turn the simple centre dial to choose from one of 48 pre-set options or customize your preferred time and temperature
  3. Press Start

What's new for you?

9-in-1

The Duo Evo Plus introduces a whole host of newness:

  • The new pressure cooker lid automatically seals when in place. Just listen for the jingle and then go and relax.
  • A new flat bottom stove top friendly inner pot is ideal for sautéing, and the two easy-grip handles ensure you can safely move it between appliances.
  • The addition of sous vide takes your culinary skills to the next level and lets you impress your guests with one of the hottest new cooking trends.

Healthy meals on the run

With the Duo Evo Plus, you can get nutritious dinners on the table quicker with cooking time up to 70% faster than traditional methods. And a one pot meal makes clean up quick and easy.

A trusted friend

The Instant Pot family always puts safety first and the Duo Evo Plus is no exception. With 10+ built-in safety features including Overheat Protection and Safety Lid Lock, the Duo Evo Plus brings the most trusted name in electric pressure cookers to your kitchen.

WITH BOTH UK AND EU (SCHUKO) POWER CABLES. UK based support function with a growing online social media community of users.

How are ratings calculated?
To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Mag
1.0 out of 5 stars The worst support experience that overrides all of the good in the product
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 8 August 2020
Verified Purchase
The instant pot is great as all the other reviewers say. I love the shorter cooking times, and the ability to leave the food cooking without having to watch the stove. It is a simply amazing product.

However I am giving a one star because of the support! I am unable to get responses to my emails, and need multiple chasers to get a single response. I reached out to obtain a replacement valve 6 weeks ago and have not received it to date. First they said they will be happy to mail it to me. But no news for another 2 weeks despite multiple chasers, after which they said they mailed it out (by normal mail). Seriously, this is such an expensive product I don’t understand why the replacement part could not have been sent via courier but I will leave it at that. 3 weeks later, I have not received anything. Support says that they will mail another one out after waiting for one more weekend but until now, it’s been another week of chasing and no response. I even offered to pay for the courier. Seriously I would have been happy to purchase a replacement valve but the one for the duo Evo plus is not available for sale. Each time, I will wait a few days to give them time to respond before I send a chaser but this has been going for the last 6 weeks. I really do not think this is a reasonable standard that we would expect from a reputable brand.

I appreciate the covid situation and that support people are working from home. But working from home does not preclude anyone from being responsive to emails. I too work from home myself and I am expected to continue to work as usual. I don’t think this is an acceptable standard for support and negatively impacts the branding.

The phone lines are not answered to as well and I am always directed to the voicemail. Please reflect on this. You can provide an extended service standard response time in Covid times, whether 2 or 3 working days or whatever longer time that is reasonable to you, but please stick to it!

There are many other pressure cookers around and I would definitely consider another one if I ever need to replace the instant pot. I can’t imagine going through the same frustration of sending multiple emails with no response.

Hazel
5.0 out of 5 stars Buy it. Buy it even if you already have one. This one is even better.
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 26 March 2020
Verified Purchase
I recently upgraded from the Duo 60 to the (COstco only) SV model. When the Evo Plus was announced I decided there were enough improvements to be worth upgrading again, even though I'd only had the SV for a couple of months.

Before I got the Evo Plus I was perfectly happy with my old Instant Pot. It was worth the upgrade.

I can't believe that I could find the Evo Plus so much better, but I do. I really do.

I love it. I love everything. I love the easier to read display. I like the fact that the id is easier to get on and is marked to show you where it goes . I like that it automatically locks. I Love the dial to choose my options and to set the timer (it's really quick to do). I love that I can see EXACTLY where it is in the process. I love the easier way of venting the ressure, and I love the new diffuser.

Best of all, I LOVE LOVE LOVE the new inner pot. We always use our inner pot on the hob, eg when making pasta, but this one HAS HANDLES!! The handles mean that when you are sauteeing in the pot, it doesn't rotate.

If you're humming and hawing about it, just DO IT!!

C.Davis
5.0 out of 5 stars Worth extra for the handles alone.
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 11 May 2020
Verified Purchase
I cannot for the life of me figure out how anyone used these before they put the handles on the insert.
This being my first pressure cooker and only having it three weeks I can’t really give an informed review but I can say it is safe, reliable, easy to use and easy to clean.
I’ve made cake, pudding, yogurt, porridge, stews, rice, grains, pot roasts and curries all with success. And when we were unable to obtain bbq charcoal a very acceptable pulled pork in 2 hours flat, that made me seriously reassess the expedience of supervising a stinky smoker for 10 hours on a Saturday.
I suggest purchasing a legitimate cookbook, there are some really dodgy video ‘cooks’ on YouTube who time after time open the lid to something that makes me feel nauseous and wonder if they are sponsored by the cornflour industry. I personally can recommend Pitre and Weinstein/Scarborough both who never ask for 1 ml more of water than is necessary and as such are conspicuously absent of post cooking thickeners, but I’m sure there are other good authors as well.

5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect pressure cooker
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 1 July 2020
Verified Purchase
What can I say? Add a bit of water, a whole chicken; then come back to a cooked chicken that's falling off of the bone!

I contemplated buying this against Sage's "fast slow pro" and the Ninja Foodi.

I rulled the Ninja out as I didn't think messing with dual lids and greasy air frying to be an actual benefit.

Personally I think the sage looks 100x better and it's auto steam release is attractive, but ultimately reviews of non-stick coatings peeling off and and a cheap plastic control front spoiled it.

Instapot's stainless steel pot (which can be used on a stove) and extras for sale sold it for me.

Cleaning is easy but there is a teeny tiny silicone cap to the pressure seal that would easily fit down our sink! I'm surprised they give you 2 large lid seals (one for sweets /savory) and none of these small cap seals?

Look forward to using it more.
